# Ways of Working: {{ display_name }}

This document defines how the team delivers fullstack features across the Symfony API (`apps/api`) and Next.js frontend (`apps/web`). Consistency here reduces coordination overhead and keeps both sides of the stack in sync.

---

## Fullstack Definition of Done

A feature is **done** when all of the following are true:

### Backend (Symfony)
- [ ] Entity and migration created/updated and tested against a real database
- [ ] API endpoint implemented and returns the correct HTTP status codes
- [ ] Server-side validation in place (Symfony Validator constraints)
- [ ] Unit tests cover the Service/{% if use_ddd %}Domain {% endif %}layer
- [ ] Integration test covers the HTTP endpoint via `WebTestCase`
- [ ] OpenAPI annotations{% if api_style == "api-platform" %} (or API Platform attributes){% endif %} are accurate
- [ ] No `var_dump`, `dd()`, or debug output left in code

### Shared Types
- [ ] `packages/shared-types` updated to reflect any new or changed response shape
{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
- [ ] Types regenerated (`pnpm --filter shared-types generate`) and committed
{% endif %}

### Frontend (Next.js)
- [ ] Service function in `src/services/` calls the new endpoint
- [ ] Page/component renders loading and error states
- [ ] Form validation mirrors backend constraints (client-side UX, not a security measure)
- [ ] No TypeScript errors (`pnpm tsc --noEmit` passes)
- [ ] Component tests written for interactive components

### Cross-Cutting
- [ ] All lint checks pass (`composer lint` + `pnpm lint`)
- [ ] No `.env` files or secrets committed
- [ ] Documentation updated if the change affects architecture or the API contract
- [ ] PR reviewed by at least one other team member
- [ ] Feature tested in a staging/preview environment end-to-end

