## API-First Workflow

Every fullstack feature follows this order. **Never build the frontend against a stubbed API if the real endpoint can be built first.**

```
1. DESIGN
   Agree on the API shape: endpoint URL, request body, response fields.
   Write or update the relevant section in docs/api-contract.md.

2. BACKEND
   Implement the Symfony endpoint.
   Write integration tests that document the exact JSON shape.
   Deploy to staging or run locally.

3. SHARED TYPES
   {% if api_style == "api-platform" %}Regenerate shared-types from the live OpenAPI spec.{% else %}Update packages/shared-types/src/index.ts by hand.{% endif %}
   Commit the updated types file in the same PR as the API work.

4. FRONTEND
   Implement the service function and UI against the real API.
   The TypeScript compiler enforces the contract.

5. REVIEW
   PR includes both backend and frontend changes where possible (atomic cross-app PR).
   Reviewer checks the API contract doc, not just the code.
```

This order means the backend is the source of truth and the frontend adapts to it - never the other way around.

