## Branching Strategy

We use **trunk-based development** with short-lived feature branches off `main`.

### Branch Naming

```
feature/<ticket-id>-<short-description>    # new functionality
fix/<ticket-id>-<short-description>        # bug fixes
chore/<description>                        # tooling, deps, refactoring
docs/<description>                         # documentation only
migration/<description>                    # database migration changes
```

### Workflow

1. Cut a branch from `main` (always up to date)
2. Make small, focused commits - prefer one logical change per commit
3. Open a PR as a draft early (link the ticket)
4. Move to "Ready for Review" when the DoD checklist is met
5. Request at least one reviewer
6. Squash-merge into `main` after approval
7. Delete the branch; staging deploys automatically

