## Deployment Pipeline

Both apps are deployed from `main`. The backend deploys first.

```
1. API tests pass (PHPUnit)
2. Deploy Symfony to production
3. Run database migrations (php bin/console doctrine:migrations:migrate --no-interaction)
4. Smoke-test API health endpoint
5. Frontend tests pass (Vitest{% if test_strategy == "full-pyramid" %} + Playwright{% endif %})
6. Deploy Next.js to production
7. Verify frontend loads and can authenticate
```

**Why backend first?** The database migration must complete before the new frontend code tries to use the new fields. The old frontend is forwards-compatible by design (it ignores unknown fields).

**Backwards compatibility rule:** An API change is **never** allowed to break the currently deployed frontend. If a breaking change is unavoidable, deploy both apps simultaneously (blue/green or feature flag).

