## AI Collaboration Guidelines

{% if ai_context %}
This project ships with `AI_CONTEXT.md` designed for AI coding agents (Claude Code, Copilot Workspace, etc.).

### For AI Agents

- Read `AI_CONTEXT.md` before starting any task
- Read `docs/api-contract.md` before touching any data flow
- Follow the API-first workflow above - never build a frontend without a matching API endpoint
- Update `packages/shared-types` whenever an API response changes
- Write tests; do not skip them for "simple" changes
- Create an ADR when introducing a new library or pattern

### For Developers Working with AI

- Scope prompts to one logical change at a time (e.g. "add the GET /users/:id endpoint" is better than "add user management")
- Reference specific files: "follow the pattern in `src/Controller/HealthController.php`"
- Review AI-generated code against the same DoD checklist as human code
- If the AI changes `packages/shared-types`, verify the Symfony output and the frontend service are consistent
- Update `AI_CONTEXT.md` when conventions change
{% else %}
When using AI coding assistants:

- Provide the contents of `docs/api-contract.md` as context
- Specify which app is in scope (api or web)
- Reference existing controller or service files as style examples
- Review generated code against the DoD checklist
{% endif %}
